# Local release-signing config for the Android workforce app.
#
# The Gradle build resolves each value from (in order):
#   1. process environment    (preferred for CI)
#   2. -P gradle property     (e.g. ./gradlew -PWORKFORCE_KEY_ALIAS=...)
#   3. local.properties       (preferred for a single operator's machine)
#
# `local.properties` is already gitignored by the Android Studio template.
# This file is a copy-pastable example only — do not commit a populated
# `local.properties` or any `*.jks` / `*.keystore` file.
#
# Variable names (all four are required to produce a Play-uploadable AAB):
#
#   WORKFORCE_KEYSTORE_FILE      Absolute path to the JKS file.
#   WORKFORCE_KEYSTORE_PASSWORD  JKS file password.
#   WORKFORCE_KEY_ALIAS          Alias inside the JKS.
#   WORKFORCE_KEY_PASSWORD       Per-alias password.
#
# Optional TLS pinning (Task #43) — leave the pins var blank to disable:
#
#   WORKFORCE_CERT_PIN_HOST      Hostname being pinned (default: workforce.tanaqolapp.com)
#   WORKFORCE_CERT_PINS          Comma-separated sha256/<base64> pin set.
#
# To generate a fresh upload keystore (one-time, then archive securely):
#   keytool -genkeypair -v \
#     -keystore upload-keystore.jks \
#     -alias workforce-upload \
#     -keyalg RSA -keysize 2048 -validity 10000 \
#     -storetype JKS
#
# After enrolling in Play App Signing, this is your *upload* key only —
# Google holds the actual app-signing key. See docs/android-release-runbook.md.

WORKFORCE_KEYSTORE_FILE=/absolute/path/to/upload-keystore.jks
WORKFORCE_KEYSTORE_PASSWORD=CHANGE_ME
WORKFORCE_KEY_ALIAS=workforce-upload
WORKFORCE_KEY_PASSWORD=CHANGE_ME
